# Design Token Usage

## Spacing Tokens

When creating or changing components that use spacing tokens (e.g., `p-4`, `m-8`, `gap-12`), always specify in comments that spacing tokens are mapped to pixel values where the number equals the pixel value:

- `p-4` = 4px padding
- `m-8` = 8px margin
- `gap-12` = 12px gap
- `spacing-16` = 16px

**Example:**

```astro
<!-- p-4 = 4px padding -->
<div class="p-4">
  Content
</div>
```

This helps maintain clarity about the actual pixel values being used, as spacing tokens map directly to pixels (e.g., `px-4` is 4px).
